 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#333333>(11/13/02 9:33:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=822.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Silly</span><hr size=1> Sorry thats a silly comparison Alucard...why would you complain if something gets BETTER?<br>
<br>
Mages have called the 50+ fire pets useless (or mostly so) since they were in the game, because these pets ARE worse than the pre 50 ones.<br>
<br>
The fire pets until 50 always had the weakness of their low hitpoints, and the advantage of their strong damage shield.<br>
<br>
The 50+ fire pets have the weakness of their low hitpoints, and NO advantage why you would use them (root? dispel? low level damage spells in a range that the water pet does?). They stun somewhat good (but even that is covered by another pet already), but you give up an enormous amount of damage to get those stuns. So WHAT is the point of the higher level fire pets?<br>
<br>
Pre 50 we have four pets to choose from. At higher level the fire pet is NO choice for the serious mage.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryotv>RyotV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(11/13/02 10:50:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=822.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Silly</span><hr size=1> But, I'm not complaining.<br>
I was just wondering why something that is inherent to a<br>
pet pre 50 is removed. None of the other pets had<br>
something removed from them, just more abilities added.<br>
<br>
I guess I will just suffer with my own ignorance.<br>
<br>
Sorry for bugging you.<br>
<br>
Budrick<br>
<br>
Living on Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fanaskin>fanaskin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(11/13/02 10:57:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=822.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   post 50 fire pets DO cast fire elemental aura</span><hr size=1> the problem however is they have a choice between fire aura and okeil's radiation. it seems 99/100 times they will cast okeil's radiation on themselves ( this is most likely 100% a bug and its original desgin was to have it only cast okeil's on other pets ). thanks to the fact that /pet report health now tells exactly what buffs a pet has now I found out after testing my new fire pet for a whole night that the fire pet DID cast fire elemental aura on itself once and ive never gotten it to do it again. so it seems that fire elemental aura is something that the post 50 fire pets CAN cast but it keep choosing to cast okeil's on itself. i suppose someone could dispell his shield all day until it cast fire elemental arua but this is definatly a bug imho. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sharkeyy>sharkeyy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://banners.steakandcheese.com/sncbutton.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/14/02 12:25:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=822.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: post 50 fire pets DO cast fire elemental aura</span><hr size=1> The post 50 fire pets are not useless anymore you just have to know how to use them.  Since the patch a while back when NPC are now *smart* casters, the fire pets now act like a sweet wiz.  From what I have gathered there are about four varations types of fire pet (using the Greater Voceration as pet) these are 1) Nuker 2) Rooter 3) Stunner 4) AE<br>
<br>
The nuker is generic... you all know what it does.<br>
While the rooter nukes, it also roots a decent amount with some of the higher level root line of spells.<br>
The stunner uses the wizzy line of stun more often than the nuke version of the pet, each use both stuns and DD, just one uses the catagory more than the other.<br>
while the ae pet i've only seen while aeing things, i am not sure if it is a *flavour* of pet, or if the pet just realizes what you are doing and does aes.  the aes arent big, but i have seen them do ae stuns and ae nukes along with a rain. <br>
I am interested in testing the new fire pet out, which shouldhave a very nice line of spells lined up for it because it being lvl 60 and all.... Just think.... Goabner begins to cast GSS.... heehee...<br>
<br>
<br>
Yaksa &quot;Love is all you need&quot; LoveCraft <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.users.drew.edu/cpetrey/wonka-youlose2.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://mailto:cpetrey@drew.edu">Master Yaksa LoveCraft</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->60 Mage Luclin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Member of Legacy of Sorrow</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sitting on the bed or lying wide awake<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->There're demons in my head and it's more than I can take<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->I think I'm on a roll but I think it's kinda weak<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Saying all I know is I gotta get away from</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kinelaria>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 473<br> <font color=#333333>(11/14/02 1:14:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=822.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: post 50 fire pets DO cast fire elemental aura</span><hr size=1> From what I've read, Child of Ro (level 63 fire pet), casts the same spells Voc: Fire and GVoc: Fire cast.<br>
<br>
Up to about 60, they can be handy in some areas. Beyond 60 though, they become pretty useless. They cast level 20ish wizard stuns. Near as I can tell, these stuns have not been updated, till I see otherwise, I'll assume they follow the old stun rules. You can check Lucy's on this, none of the stuns this pet casts have been changed, while higher level stuns have now been flagged to be able to stun targets over level 55. So for stunning purposes, on mobs over 55, you have to use an air pet, and that's assuming the mob isn't immune to stun to begin with (not uncommon with high level mobs).<br>
<br>
If I want a pet that will chain root, I'll use the earth pet. It does that fairly well, and backs it up with some decent damage.<br>
<br>
The chain nuking one is worthless, a regular melee pet will easily outdamage a fire pet chain casting low level wizard nukes.<br>
<br>
The pet AE'ing has always bugged me. Not just because it's casting a really crappy low level AE, but also because this will break mezzes. That makes it dangerous. Thankfully it doesn't seem to AE much, in fact, quite rarely. I'd prefer it not to AE at all though.<br>
<br>
The 52/58 pets can be useful at times, but most of the time they're simply not as good as a regular pet. The 63 pet is totally worthless, the one good aspect to the wizard pet pre-60 was it's stunning ability. Since at the level you get this spell, you will most likely be fighting level 60+ mobs, that abiltiy does nothing.<br>
<br>
Shame the 63 pet wasn't using just damage spells, of a higher level than the 52 and 58 pets. if it was putting out alot of damage via spells, it'd have given us a good pet against bane only mobs, or mobs with huge AC.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
